26:05.958 --> 26:19.114
Do you think about John the Baptist, a prophet who went to King Herod Antipas and would publicly call him out for the sin of stealing his brother's wife?

26:21.337 --> 26:22.258
When the believers

26:22.658 --> 26:37.660
of God, when they believed there were set-apart people, they had this prophetic edge that called out sin, called out wrong, called out immorality, because they were calling people into an alignment with God's vision for the world.

26:38.782 --> 26:43.249
Living a prayerful and peaceful life does not abdicate our prophetic witness.

26:44.471 --> 26:52.082
It rather emboldens it, gives credibility to it, that we are a people who carry out God's vision

26:52.226 --> 26:53.567
before the world.

26:54.689 --> 26:56.711
And that's what the church has done in the last 2000 years.

26:57.872 --> 26:59.794
And communism was making its way through Europe.

27:00.615 --> 27:03.858
It was a Christians who stood up and said, no, this is oppressive.

27:04.299 --> 27:07.562
This censorship will be destructive and they stood against it.

27:08.624 --> 27:11.126
But Nazism was moving through Germany.

27:11.787 --> 27:22.098
It was meant like Dietrich Bonheiffer and women like Corey Tamboum, who refused to give government total authority and power because they saw this to be destructive for people.

27:23.426 --> 27:28.151
when William Wilberforce in the 19th century saw the transatlantic slave trade.

27:28.671 --> 27:32.115
He said, this does not bode well with God's vision for people.

27:32.295 --> 27:33.917
His image bearers, this is wrong.

27:34.938 --> 27:39.382
So he led campaigns that would end slavery in the British Empire.

27:40.323 --> 27:45.208
Dr. King carried such a prophetic witness during the civil rights movement.

27:45.849 --> 27:51.314
And women like Mother Teresa and Amy Carmichael and Catherine Booth and Lottie Moon

27:51.618 --> 27:58.508
They saw the oppression of the widows and the orphans and the marginalized and the poor, and they said, this is not God's vision for the world.

27:58.688 --> 28:02.073
So they walked in this prophetic witness for the world.

28:02.513 --> 28:14.570
People have used, the church has used, their influence, their stays, their voice to invite the world, to call the world into God's vision for it, and we must do the same today.

28:15.672 --> 28:20.178
What you see across 2,000 years is that a prophetic church

28:20.866 --> 28:23.809
shapes the conscience of the world.

28:24.930 --> 28:27.593
A prophetic church shapes the conscience of the world.

28:28.134 --> 28:37.324
Hear me, the church of Jesus did not set out first and foremost to change laws, but to change conscience.

28:37.344 --> 28:46.834
To change the way people thought, saw the world, saw each other, laws came as a result of a changed heart, the church,

28:46.946 --> 28:51.013
saw that indwelled by the Holy Spirit, they could change the very conscience of the world.

28:51.293 --> 28:54.598
And a great example of this is with infanticide in the first century.

28:55.620 --> 29:05.136
It was the time of the Roman Empire that I just mentioned a few minutes ago, for children because of their gender, mostly because of their female, or because of the economic condition of a family.

29:05.717 --> 29:13.970
Children were left in the sun, they called it death by exposure, left in the sun to dry and die.

29:16.514 --> 29:19.997
in fantasy, normal expected of families in first century.

29:20.658 --> 29:22.700
But the Christians believed differently.

29:23.481 --> 29:26.904
They believed in the value and sanctity of all human life.

29:27.024 --> 29:28.025
And so what would they do?

29:28.045 --> 29:29.146
They would go and pick up these children.

29:29.166 --> 29:32.129
They would follow parents or dads who were throwing these kids away.

29:32.470 --> 29:38.716
And here we just go and pick them up, adopt them as their own, bring them into their churches, bring them into their families.

29:39.496 --> 29:45.202
Many people say if you walked into your first century church, you would hear so loudly the sound of singing girls.

29:46.178 --> 29:52.925
Girls who are rescued from the street because Christians held onto the value of human life.

29:54.146 --> 30:01.012
They began to teach about how God values every single person, how God values life.

30:01.833 --> 30:14.866
They, in teaching so, began to change the conscience of the world so much so that in 318 A.D., Constantine would declare that infanticide was now a crime.

30:15.426 --> 30:22.215
And every historian says this happened because across the last two or three centuries, Christians taught differently than the rest of the world.

30:22.515 --> 30:25.660
And it changed the conscience of the world.

30:25.700 --> 30:32.008
Should we be after laws and legislation that are righteous and just absolutely?

30:33.210 --> 30:37.315
But if a law is changed without a heart being changed, it won't last.

30:38.517 --> 30:40.059
It's limited in its transformation.

30:40.359 --> 30:42.642
So yes, we should pray and hope for the right laws.

30:42.786 --> 30:57.902
But the church is first and foremost called to enlighten the hearts of people, to open up the conscience of humanity by the power of the Spirit of God, to think differently, to imagine the world differently, to value people differently.

30:58.182 --> 31:04.549
And when conscience changes, then laws will permanently change for the good and flourishing of all humanity.

31:05.530 --> 31:09.234
This is the prophetic witness of the church.

31:09.698 --> 31:14.224
that calls a role into right alignment with God's heart and his vision.

31:15.366 --> 31:16.908
You may be thinking, well, I don't know how to do that.

31:17.549 --> 31:22.676
I don't have the resources or influence or the titles to do that, but at least to my fourth point.

31:22.696 --> 31:25.420
We're not just prayerful and peaceful and prophetic.

31:25.880 --> 31:29.826
We are powerful as a church of Jesus, powerful.

31:31.088 --> 31:33.471
We have a source of power.

31:33.811 --> 31:38.578
